A vintage 1990s-style illustration of a well-organized wooden workbench viewed from above, featuring neatly arranged floppy disks, CD-ROMs, and a chunky beige external hard drive connected by tangled cables. A worn leather tool roll lies open revealing small screwdrivers and tweezers. Scattered across the warm oak surface are colorful software installer discs emerging from paper sleeves, a dusty USB memory stick, and a handwritten checklist on yellowed paper with checkmarks. Warm afternoon sunlight streams through a nearby window casting long shadows. The scene evokes nostalgic ritual and methodical preparation, like a craftsman laying out tools before beginning careful restoration work. Muted earth tones with pops of jewel-colored disc reflections.
